<div class="g--row g--row-1">
<div class="g--col-1 g--column g--content g--row-1 g--two-third">
<ol>
	<li>Use two colors to shade the rectangle so there are 2&#xA0;square units of one color for every 1&#xA0;square unit of the other color.</li>
	<li>
	<p>The rectangle you just colored has an area of 24 square units. Draw a different shape that does <em>not</em> have an area of 24 square units, but that can also be shaded with two colors in a <span class="math math-repaired">\(2:1\)</span> ratio. Shade your new shape using two colors.</p>
